<center><font size=7><b>Death Wish 3</b></font></center>
<center>Number of entries found: 4</center><p>
<center>
<table width=600>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Tips</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>The first and most important thing is to shoot the thugs only.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Don't shoot the women or the medics, as these can't be killed and only
waste ammo.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Don't shoot Grannies, tables, chairs or TVs - you lose points for grannies
and get no points for furniture.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Don't shoot too many cops, 'cos when you've cleared the street of thugs,
the cops swarm the streets shooting at you, and your injury level shoots
up.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;When your injury level is high, enter a house and find a room where you&nbsp;can
see both sides.  No thugs or cops can enter the room to harm you, so you
can just stand still until your injuries go down.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;It's best to go after the gang leaders only when you have two or three
weapons with a lot of ammo, because the thugs cover the streets and a lot
of ammo is needed to clear them.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To conserve ammo while walking around the streets, use a hand gun.  This
uses fifty rounds which fire off very slowly, making it last longer.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;To clear crowd scenes, let off short bursts of machine gun fire.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Wait to see if the thugs fall down, 'cos they take a while, and you don't
want to waste bullets if they're already hit.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Save the rocket launcher for when you meet a gang leader, to clear the
thugs around him.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Shotguns have limited ammo, fire quickly and are handy if you don't have a
machine gun.<br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;One last thing, shoot out all the windows to gain extra points.
 <i>(YS Smash Tips)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Multiface pokes</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD><table border="0">
<tr>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>DESCRIPTION</B></U></TD>
<td WIDTH="200" ALIGN="LEFT"><B><U>POKE(s)</B></U></TD>
</TR>
<tr><td>No Injury</td><td>39856,201</td></tr>
<tr><td>Infinite Ammo</td><td>38678,175:39253,175</td></tr>
<tr><td>No Back Stabbing</td><td>41734,0</td></tr>
</table><br>

&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <i>(Gerard Sweeney in Hack Attack III)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
<TR><TD bgcolor="blue" background=""><font color="white"><b><i>Type-in hacks</i></b></font></td></tr>
<TR><TD>This can be found in <a href="ftp://ftp.void.jump.org/pub/sinclair/magazines/SinclairUser/Issue74/Tape/">this issue of Poke City</a>.
 <i>(Cover Tape in Sinclair User issue 74)</i> 

<br><hr>
<pre>
 10 CLEAR 24575: LOAD ""CODE
 20 FOR n=33543 TO 1e9
 30 READ a
 40 IF a<999 THEN POKE n,a: NEXT n
 50 POKE 33019,131: PRINT USR 32768
 60 DATA 33,0,64,49,255,95,17,0,128,1,0,4, 237,176
 70 DATA 62,201,50,176,155: REM NO INJURY
 80 DATA 62,175,50,22,151,50,185,153,: INFINITE AMMO
 90 DATA 175,50,6,163: REM NO BACKSTABBING
100 DATA 195,64,108,999: REM END MARKER!
</pre>
 <i>(YS Smash Tips)</i> 
<br>
</td></tr>
